    "articleNumber": 6,
    "language": "english",
    "title": "How can I manage my symptoms naturally?",
    "summary": "While some women choose to take medicine from a doctor, many find great relief by making small \"lifestyle\" changes. These are natural ways to help your body find its balance again as your hormones shift. You don’t nee...",
    "content": "Working With Your Body\n\nWhile some women choose to take medicine from a doctor, many find great relief by making\nsmall \"lifestyle\" changes. These are natural ways to help your body find its balance again as\nyour hormones shift.\n\n1. Beating the Heat (Hot Flashes)\n\nYou don’t need a fancy machine to cool down. Try these \"Low-Tech\" tips:\n\n   ● The \"Sip and Cool\" Method: Keep a bottle of cold water with you. When you feel a hot\n      flash starting, take slow sips. It helps cool your core temperature from the inside out.\n   ● Dress in Natural Fibers: In Nepal, we have beautiful cotton and bamboo fabrics.\n      These \"breathe\" much better than synthetic materials like nylon or polyester, which trap\n      heat against your skin.\n   ● Identify Your \"Triggers\": Notice if your hot flashes happen after eating spicy food (like\n      extra chilly in your tarkari), drinking very hot tea, or feeling stressed. Try to reduce these\n      triggers for a few days to see if you feel better.\n\n2. Calming the Mind (Deep Breathing)\n\nWhen a hot flash or a wave of anxiety hits, your heart rate goes up. You can \"trick\" your body\ninto calming down:\n\n   ● The 4-7-8 Breath: Breathe in for 4 seconds, hold for 7, and exhale slowly for 8. This tells\n      your nervous system, \"We are safe, you can relax now.\"\n\n3. Strengthening Your Bones\n\nSince you are losing estrogen, your bones can become \"brittle\" (like dry wood).\n\n   ● Sunlight: Nepal has beautiful sunshine! Spending 15–20 minutes in the sun helps your\n      body make Vitamin D, which is essential for keeping your bones strong.\n   ● Weight-Bearing Activity: You don't need a gym. Carrying groceries, gardening, or\n      walking up stairs are all \"natural\" ways to keep your bones dense and healthy.\n\n4. Herbal Support (With Caution)\n\nMany women use traditional herbs. While some find them helpful, always check with a health\nprofessional first:\n\n  ● Shatavari: A common herb in Ayurvedic traditions often used to support female\n     hormonal health.\n  ● Flaxseeds: These contain \"lignans\" which can act like a very weak, natural estrogen.\n\n    Important Note: \"Natural\" doesn't always mean \"harmless.\" If you are taking other\n    medications for blood pressure or diabetes, always talk to a doctor before starting\n    new herbal supplements.",
